HEADWORD: Inurn
<hw>In*urn"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Inurned</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Inurning</conjf>.]</vmorph> <def>To put in an urn, as the ashes
of the dead; hence, to bury; to intomb.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The sepulcher⟦br⟧
Wherein we saw thee quietly <qex>inurned</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

